title: Tulsi Gabbard calls out lying politicians: 'No greater form of disrespect of democracy'
description: Former Rep. Tulsi Gabbard, previously a Democrat, calls out Rep.-elect George Santos over his series of deception on Thursday's "Tucker Carlson Tonight."

title: JJ Watt reveals hilarious voice memo from Cardinals rookie who learned of his retirement
description: Arizona Cardinals defensive end J.J. Watt revealed a certain voice memo by rookie linebacker Jesse Luketa, who learned of his retirement after getting his wisdom teeth out.

title: Sofia Vergara, Brooke Burke and more celebs heat up Christmas week in sizzling bikinis
description: Some celebrities spent Christmas on the beach this year. Molly Sims and Gisele Bündchen opened gifts in swimsuits and flip-flops while on tropical vacations.

title: Los Angeles prosecutor pens scathing exit letter to progressive DA George Gascon: ‘Managerial dumpster fire’
description: A veteran Los Angeles County prosecutor criticized District Attorney George Gascon on his last day in a long letter in which he aired his grievances.

title: South Carolina Waffle House employee fends off armed attackers with pistol: police
description: A Waffle House employee in South Carolina fended off two attackers with a gun, police said

title: Titans expected to start QB Josh Dobbs; Malik Willis to serve as backup against the Cowboys
description: The Titans are making another change at quarterback ahead of their primetime matchup against the Dallas Cowboys, giving Joshua Dobbs starting quarterback duty.

title: Arizona bill would require teachers get parents' permission to use students' 'preferred pronoun'
description: An Arizona state legislator filed a bill that would prohibit teachers from referring to students as their preferred pronouns without parental consent.

title: MSNBC contributor Katty Kay was 'appalled' her kids refused COVID boosters before holidays
description: An MSNBC contributor voiced disbelief after her children reportedly refused to have further vaccinations against COVID before the holidays.

title: Oregon, Washington hit with deadly storms, flooding
description: A winter storm that brought powerful wind gusts to Oregon and Washington state on Tuesday resulted in at least four deaths as extreme weather hit the Pacific Northwest.

title: Moab murders: Utah suspect's 'significant other' knew about slayings for months and kept quiet, police reveal
description: Moab murder suspect Adam Pinkusiewicz had a 'significant other' who knew about the double shooting but did not come forward, police revealed Thursday.

title: Bob Penny, 'Sweet Home Alabama' and 'Forrest Gump' actor, dead at 87
description: Dr. Robert "Bob" Lynn Penny, an actor who played roles in "My Cousin Vinny" and "Mississippi Burning," died Sunday in Alabama at the age of 87.

title: Sen. Cardin: If you 'espouse hate,' you're 'not protected' by the First Amendment
description: Sen. Ben Cardin, D-Md., faced massive backlash after suggesting that hate speech is not protected under the First Amendment during a Senate Committee Hearing on Wednesday.
